node.text:
Dear little me:

Enjoy the little moments. Time goes by a lot quicker than you think and you can’t get it back. Be grateful for as much as you can. Don’t let the bad stuff steal the good. Life is unfair sometimes and people can be just as awful as they can be great, but know that we will all answer to God one day. He will turn everything the enemy meant for evil and turn it around for your good if you let Him. Use your free will wisely. 

Just keep forgiving as much as you can to keep your heart free of poison and fear, and remember forgiveness doesn’t equal trust. Life is too short to live angry or resentful. Boundaries are beautiful. Who cares what people think? 

I promise knowing and loving Jesus is the only way to true lasting freedom and eternal life, and He is who He says He is. He will reveal Himself to you as you seek Him with your whole heart. Once you taste of Him, you will want everyone to know this love. Even if it costs you everything, it will be worth it. Nothing satisfies like the love of God and knowing Him personally. 

Don’t be so hard on yourself. We are all learning. Every morning is a new chance for a fresh start. 

Forgive fast, love hard, and keep it moving. Love wins. Always. 

————-

For I know the plans I have for you,” declares the Lord, “plans to prosper you and not to harm you, plans to give you hope and a future. Jeremiah 29:11

node.text: Happy 27th birthday Justin. I am so grateful you were born and blessed to be your mom. You bring me and this whole world such incredible joy. I’m proud of you for too many reasons to list here, and I love you more than you may ever know. I hope you have a phenomenal year and may you live happily ever after. ❤️

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Pattie Mallette on February 17, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and big cat.

node.text:
It’s been awhile! Thought I’d say hello.  Been trying to figure out life outside of social media as much as possible and doing my best to avoid drama— (not an easy task these days). 

I recently came back to Canada for a little while until things are not as crazy and unpredictable. Enjoying family and rediscovering my roots and parts of who I am that may have gotten a little lost along the way. I’m also enjoying the rest and slower pace of life. I’m only ever a plane ride away. 

It’s a difficult time for so many. My heart goes out to all of you who have been suffering or have lost loved ones as of late. I am praying for better days to come. I know for me, Jesus makes everything more bearable. I don’t know how anyone copes without His love and comfort. 

Please leave a comment of something positive you’re learning or doing now in spite of all the hardship, sadness and darkness in the world today. We need more light and hope. Tell me something happy or something you have overcome. 

Xo Love and hugs.

node.text:
Happy birthday Mom! 70 looks AMAZING on you!!!! 🎉

I can’t IMAGINE my life without you in it. I’m unbelievably grateful you were born! I’m even more grateful God picked you to be my mother! There is no one like you! You’re a queen. You have always been there for me even when I didn’t deserve it. You always loved me unconditionally. You taught me how to forgive fast and love hard and leave the past where it is (and belongs). You taught me how to fight for what’s right at all costs. You always taught me that life is what we make it with what we are given to work with. You taught me that joy and peace were better than misery and bitterness. You never stayed mad or sad for too long. You have modeled honesty and integrity and loyalty for as long as I can remember. I am proud to be your daughter. You are strong and radiant and trustworthy and faithful and reliable! There is no one like you Mommy! I hope you plan on sticking around several more decades!! We love you and need you. I hope this year / decade is the best yet!! 

I love you more every day mom! Xo

#happybirthday #happy70th #christmasevebaby #happybirthdaymom
